<subSubSection pageNumber="894" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="894">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="894">
Note: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crispum">Trichomanes crispum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, with the type designated by Proctor, was proposed as conserved type of the genus by Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="894">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 571. 1992). The Committee for Pteridophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="894">Taxon</emphasis>
48: 133. 1999) recommended conservation as proposed, and it was approved by the General Committee (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="894">Taxon 48</emphasis>
: 377. 1999). However, subsequent Codes have not listed the Plumier plate (proposed as the 
<typeStatus>
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
</typeStatus>
), so the plate is a 
<typeStatus>
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
</typeStatus>
, rather than a conserved type.
</paragraph>
